.SH "NAME"
Net::DNS::RR::TXT \- DNS TXT resource record
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&    use Net::DNS;
\&    $rr = new Net::DNS::RR( \*(Aqname TXT  txtdata ...\*(Aq );
\&
\&    $rr = new Net::DNS::RR( name    => \*(Aqname\*(Aq,
\&                            type    => \*(AqTXT\*(Aq,
\&                            txtdata => \*(Aqsingle text string\*(Aq
\&                            );
\&
\&    $rr = new Net::DNS::RR( name    => \*(Aqname\*(Aq,
\&                            type    => \*(AqTXT\*(Aq,
\&                            txtdata => [ \*(Aqmultiple\*(Aq, \*(Aqstrings\*(Aq, ... ]
\&                            );
\&
\&    use utf8;
\&    $rr = new Net::DNS::RR( \*(Aqjp TXT    古池や　蛙飛込む　水の音\*(Aq );
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Class for \s-1DNS\s0 Text (\s-1TXT\s0) resource records.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
The available methods are those inherited from the base class augmented
by the type-specific methods defined in this package.
.PP
Use of undocumented package features or direct access to internal data
structures is discouraged and could result in program termination or
