.SS "txtdata"
.IX Subsection "txtdata"
.Vb 2
\&    $string = $rr\->txtdata;
\&    @list   = $rr\->txtdata;
\&
\&    $rr\->txtdata( @list );
.Ve
.PP
When invoked in scalar context, \fBtxtdata()\fR returns the descriptive text
as a single string, regardless of the number of elements.
.PP
In a list context, \fBtxtdata()\fR returns a list of the text elements.
